  "texts": [
    "Intuition: The language portion of the human brain encapsulates a complex cognitive function that grasps the rules of grammar and sentence structure, comprehends the meaning of words and how their relationships with other words form meaningful expressions.",
    "Humans understand the broader context of a sequence of words based on topic, style, and intent.",
    "Scientists still do not know how that cognitive function of language generation works in either the brain or the LLM.",
    "However, the LLM learned a version of that complex function and will expectedly learn better approximations of it with more parameters.",
    "Predicting the next word based on probabilities led to limitations of LLMs."
  ],
